text.tspan: Rate of state-based conflicts, World, 1946 to 2008
The number of conflicts divided by the number of all states. This accounts for the changing number of states

over time. Included are
interstate
,
intrastate
, and
extrasystemic
conflicts that were ongoing that year.
Data source: Peace Research Institute Oslo (2017); Gleditsch and Ward (2007); Uppsala Conflict Data Program and Peace Research
Note: Some conflicts affect several regions. The sum across all regions can therefore be higher than the global number.
